description: Australia is no stranger to extreme weather. From heat waves and droughts to flooding rains, hailstorms or fire weather, our continent experiences it all.
title: Get set for more extreme weather across Australia this spring and summer, say meteorologists

description: For the past few years, a series of controversies have rocked the well-established field of cosmology. In a nutshell, the predictions of the standard model of the universe appear to be at odds with some recent observations.
title: Cosmology is at a tipping point—we may be on the verge of discovering new physics

description: Coelacanths are deep-sea fish that live off the coasts of southern Africa and Indonesia and can reach up to two meters in length. For a long time, scientists believed they were extinct.
title: Exceptional new fish fossil sparks a rethink of how Earth's geology drives evolution

description: Two recent studies have cast doubt on a popular theory that the ancient residents of Easter Island suffered a societal collapse because they overexploited their natural resources, an event often labeled one of history's first "ecocides".
title: 'Ecocide' on Easter Island never took place, studies suggest

description: Soap operas are known for outrageous schemes and scandalous affairs, but an NYU researcher finds that they can also serve as effective interventions for preventing intergroup violence in conflict-ridden areas by shaping social norms, promoting understanding of different perspectives, and encouraging people to create change.
title: Social messaging in soap operas can prevent violence and intergroup conflict

description: New research co-led by Cornell University examines thousands of years of Arctic sled dog ancestry and reveals when and how Siberian and Alaskan sled dogs' DNA mixed.
title: Genomics reveals sled dogs' Siberian lineage

description: Iran on Saturday blasted a new research satellite into orbit, state media said, in the latest such development for an aerospace program that has long faced Western criticism.
title: Iran says new research satellite launched into orbit

description: At a shelter for big cats in Brazil, a vet gingerly dresses wounds on a jaguar that was caught in wildfires raging in the world's largest tropical wetland.
title: Brazil vets heal burns of jaguar burned in Pantanal fire

description: One person has drowned in Poland and four people are missing in the Czech Republic, authorities said Sunday, as Storm Boris lashed central and eastern Europe with torrential rains and flooding.
title: One dead in Poland as storm lashes eastern and central Europe

description: A billionaire spacewalker returned to Earth with his crew on Sunday, ending a five-day trip that lifted them higher than anyone has traveled since NASA's moonwalkers.
title: Tech billionaire returns to Earth after first private spacewalk

description: Get ready for a partial lunar eclipse and supermoon, all rolled into one.
title: Catch a partial lunar eclipse during September's supermoon
